The paper deals with the problem of trace reconstruction, which is a problem in information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT. The paper also considers natural parameterizations and generalizations of the problem, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). Additionally, the paper presents results on reconstructing matrices and sparse strings, which could be relevant to the category of cs.LG (machine learning).
